Four people suffered minor to moderate injuries after their car crashed into a wall on the corners of Greyling and May Street in the Pietermaritzburg CBD. Mi7 National Group’s Emergency Medical Services and SAPS attended to the scene. According to Brandon Drinkwater of Mi7 National Group’s Emergency, medics found that the car had crashed into a wall with four occupants inside. “The patients were an adult male and three young schoolgirls. We stabilised them and transported them to hospital for further treatment,” said Drinkwater.